<h2><a name="make_pair" id="make_pair">make_pair</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>

Syntax:

</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">  pair<span class="sy0">&lt;</span>TYPE1<span class="sy0">,</span>TYPE2<span class="sy0">&gt;</span> make_pair<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">const</span> TYPE1 <span class="sy0">&amp;</span>a<span class="sy0">,</span> <span class="kw4">const</span> TYPE2 <span class="sy0">&amp;</span>b <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;</pre>
<p>
The make_pair function returns a single object that contains the two items <code>a</code> and <code>b</code>.  make_pair is a quick way of creating an instance of the <a href="pair" class="wikilink1" title="stl:utility:pair">pair</a> class.   
</p>

<p>
For example:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;"><span class="co2">#include &lt;string&gt;</span>
using std<span class="sy0">::</span><span class="kw4">string</span>;
<span class="co2">#include &lt;iostream&gt;</span>
using std<span class="sy0">::</span><a href="http://www.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/009695399/functions/cout.html"><span class="kw3">cout</span></a>;
<span class="co2">#include &lt;utility&gt;</span>
using std<span class="sy0">::</span><span class="me2">pair</span>;
using std<span class="sy0">::</span><span class="me2">make_pair</span>;
&nbsp;
<span class="kw4">int</span> main <span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span> <span class="br0">&#123;</span>
  pair<span class="sy0">&lt;</span>int<span class="sy0">,</span>string<span class="sy0">&gt;</span> tuple <span class="sy0">=</span> make_pair<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="nu0">42</span><span class="sy0">,</span> <span class="st0">&quot;The answer&quot;</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
&nbsp;
  <a href="http://www.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/009695399/functions/cout.html"><span class="kw3">cout</span></a> <span class="sy0">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class="st0">&quot;tuple.first: &quot;</span> <span class="sy0">&lt;&lt;</span> tuple.<span class="me1">first</span>
       <span class="sy0">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class="st0">&quot;, tuple.second: &quot;</span> <span class="sy0">&lt;&lt;</span> tuple.<span class="me1">second</span> <span class="sy0">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class="st0">'<span class="es0">\n</span>'</span>;
&nbsp;
  <span class="kw1">return</span> <span class="nu19">0</span>;
<span class="br0">&#125;</span></pre>
